  <td valign=3Dtop style=3D'padding:0cm 5.75pt 0cm 5.75pt'>
  <p class=3DMsoNormal>An atypical Ursidian, hairless, slightly short and c=
losely
  resembling a humanoid, however the likeness is mostly only in skin deep. =
<br>
  <br>
  The Visareen (used plural and singular) are a generally peaceful race, ho=
wever
  they take extreme pride in the outward show of strength. They will make g=
reat
  efforts to have a very large military, and their entire culture is based
  around Military shows, competitions and Displays. Most Visareen's will gr=
ow
  up with the desire to enter and serve in their military forces in some wa=
y. <br>
  <br>
  The Visareen's leader, Eroff Jetaah, is considered by many Visareen to be=
 a
  god, and to the rest they believe he is directly related or gifted by a
  spiritual being. This is almost entirely down to Eroff's unusual position=
 in
  that he has lived for thousands of years, the fellow members of his race
  typically expire within two hundred. As the Visareen around him revered h=
im
  as some kind of prophet in his youth he quickly become a large influence =
and
  eventually their leader. <br>
  <br>
  Eroff Jetaah is an extremely effective speaker and is very influential in=
 the
  Visareen's fascination with military power. This is partly because of a
  slightly paranoid disposition, Eroff's long, seemingly eternal life has m=
ade
  him value his own life a lot more than a normal being. This has created h=
is
  own personal desire to make the Visareen as powerful as possible to count=
er
  any threats from other races but to go to war as little as possible to re=
duce
  the risk to himself. <br>
  <br>
  The Visareen make a somewhat cold neighbour to other Empires, appearing
  threatening with their overt displays of strength but in reality they will
  rarely make any actions to invoke actual conflict. <br>
  <br>
  The Visareen live in large spread out communities all centred around their
  own temples built to hear the frequent preaching of their leader.</p>
  <p class=3DMsoNormal>The Visareen preferred weapon is the Missile and they
  focus on Power and Shields with Energy Research.</p>
  <p class=3DMsoNormal><i style=3D'mso-bidi-font-style:normal'>In game term=
s this
  race provides a different challenge than most. They need to create a good=
 war
  machine but actually not start any wars. This means as a player you would
  need to somehow expand out your empire without starting war, will you be
  drawn to invade without war and take the reputation hit? Or provoke war s=
ome
  other way?<o:p></o:p></i></p>
